      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T20:38:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I really like the syntax this will enable at the caller. My hesitation: I look at the DSL through the lens of \"if we replace all of our internal SkSL, what\u0027s the code-size delta going to be?\".\n\nWith this variadic template setup (and the calls to push_back), it seems likely the compiler will inline just about everything. If we had an initializer_list version, there could be a single implementation in the .cpp, and far less per-statement overhead in the calling code. I\u0027m not sure how that would handle the clever Expression-as-Statement thing you\u0027re doing, though - and my code-size fears may be overblown (or we may find alternate strategies to mitigate the impact). Just wanted to get this out there, as food for thought.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 50,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "3a4b13c8c768a67902a92590bebed45e4dac4df5",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
