      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T21:41:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Rather than requiring the caller to call this, shouldn\u0027t we just do it automatically on their behalf? SkSLPool internally uses the exact same tricks, but callers can just say `Pool::AllocMemory(10)` instead of the awkward `Pool::Instance().allocMemory(10)`. Pool just calls get_thread_local_memory_pool automatically for you.\n\nI would expect `DSLWriter::Context()` would flow better than `DSLWriter::Instance().context()` etc. And AFAIK there\u0027s no need to ever go outside the current thread\u0027s DSLWriter?",
